1)  Analysis of the Main Target Image

•  Total Blocks and Layers  
   – There are 9 total blocks used.  
   – They form 2 layers:  
     1. The bottom layer has 5 orange cylinders arranged in two rows of two (front and middle) plus one centered at the back.  
     2. The top layer has 4 green rectangular blocks laid side‐by‐side to form a rectangular “tabletop.”  

•  Spatial Relationships  
   – All 5 orange cylinders stand vertically and support the green blocks above.  
   – The 4 green blocks are placed in the same horizontal orientation, directly on top of (and spanning across) the columns.  

2)  Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary

•  Needed Green Blocks  
   – Use the horizontally oriented green block shown as index 1 in the dictionary (because its “length” runs left to right, matching the target).  
   – Four copies of block #1 are required.  

•  Needed Orange Blocks  
   – Use the vertically oriented orange cylinder shown as index 7 for each column.  
   – Five copies of block #7 are required.  

3)  Assembly Order

Below is one possible step‐by‐step sequence (placing the five cylinders first, then the four rectangular blocks):

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 7
  Step2:  Move block with index 7
  Step3:  Move block with index 7
  Step4:  Move block with index 7
  Step5:  Move block with index 7
  Step6:  Move block with index 1
  Step7:  Move block with index 1
  Step8:  Move block with index 1
  Step9:  Move block with index 1
}
